# Dashboard Structure

The dashboard is Portal's main business interface providing comprehensive CRM and business management tools.

## Layout Architecture

### Core Layout Components
- `app/[locale]/dashboard/layout.tsx`: Protected dashboard layout with authentication
- `app/[locale]/dashboard/page.tsx`: Dashboard homepage with analytics overview
- `components/dashboard/header.tsx`: Main header with breadcrumbs and search
- `components/dashboard/sidebar.tsx`: Collapsible navigation sidebar

### Navigation Structure
The dashboard uses a sidebar-based navigation with collapsible sections:
- **CRM**: Contact and company management
- **Workspace**: Tasks and calendar
- **Resources**: Content and email management 
- **Advance**: Site and admin controls
- **Account**: User preferences and settings

## Feature Sections

### CRM Management
**Contact Management** (`/dashboard/crm/contacts`):
- Contact list with advanced filtering and search
- Contact details with activity timeline
- Bulk operations and import/export
- Contact assignment and ownership
- Lead scoring and conversion tracking

**Company Management** (`/dashboard/crm/company`):
- Company profiles with contact relationships
- Company hierarchy and subsidiaries
- Revenue tracking and deal management
- Company activity and interaction history

**Team Management** (`/dashboard/crm/team`):
- Team member management and roles
- Performance analytics and reporting
- Collaboration tools and shared resources
- Team activity feeds and notifications

### Workspace Tools
**Task Management** (`/dashboard/workspace/tasks`):
- Kanban board with drag-and-drop
- Task assignment and status tracking
- Priority levels and due date management
- Task dependencies and subtasks
- Team collaboration on tasks

**Calendar System** (`/dashboard/workspace/calendar`):
- Multiple view modes (month, week, day)
- Event creation and management
- Meeting scheduling with participants
- Calendar sharing and permissions
- Integration with contact activities

### Resource Management
**Content Management** (`/dashboard/resource/content`):
- Content library and organization
- Rich text editor for content creation
- Content versioning and approval workflows
- Template management for reusable content

**Email Templates** (`/dashboard/resource/emails`):
- Email template builder with drag-and-drop
- Template categorization and tagging
- Personalization and dynamic content
- Email performance analytics

### Advanced Features
**Site Management** (`/dashboard/advance/site`):
- General site settings and configuration
- User management and permissions
- System health and monitoring
- Integration settings and API keys

**Admin Controls** (`/dashboard/advance/site/(admin)`):
- Advanced user management
- System configuration and maintenance
- Audit logs and compliance reporting
- Database management tools

### Account Management
**User Settings** (`/dashboard/account/settings`):
- Personal profile management
- Password and security settings
- Notification preferences
- Timezone and locale settings

**Account Preferences** (`/dashboard/account`):
- Dashboard customization
- Theme and appearance settings
- API key management
- Export and backup options

## Component Architecture

### Dashboard Components
```tsx
// Main dashboard layout structure
<SidebarProvider>
  <DashboardSidebar />
  <SidebarInset>
    <DashboardHeader />
    <main>{children}</main>
  </SidebarInset>
</SidebarProvider>
```

### Navigation Patterns
- Breadcrumb navigation for page hierarchy
- Command palette for quick actions (Cmd+K)
- Contextual actions in page headers
- Quick access to frequently used features

### Data Display Patterns
- Interactive data tables with sorting and filtering
- Card-based layouts for overview screens
- Timeline views for activity tracking
- Chart and analytics visualizations

## State Management

### tRPC Integration
- Real-time data synchronization
- Optimistic updates for better UX
- Error handling and retry logic
- Background data refetching

### Local State Management
- React Query for server state caching
- Local state for UI interactions
- Form state management with React Hook Form
- Global UI state (sidebar, themes, etc.)

## Performance Optimizations

### Code Splitting
- Route-based code splitting for dashboard sections
- Component lazy loading for heavy features
- Dynamic imports for optional functionality

### Data Loading
- Pagination for large datasets
- Virtual scrolling for long lists
- Background data prefetching
- Intelligent caching strategies

## Responsive Design

### Mobile Adaptation
- Collapsible sidebar for mobile devices
- Touch-optimized interactions
- Simplified navigation for small screens
- Progressive disclosure of features

### Desktop Optimization
- Multi-panel layouts for large screens
- Keyboard shortcuts for power users
- Drag and drop interactions
- Context menus and right-click actions

## Security & Permissions

### Role-Based Access
- Different dashboard views based on user roles
- Feature-level permissions enforcement
- Data access restrictions by ownership
- Audit logging for sensitive operations

### Data Protection
- Client-side data validation
- Secure API communication
- Session timeout handling
- CSRF protection on forms
